{"questionId":"22631402","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>To comply with safety regulations, Andrew updates this design. The start of the design will stay the same. Then, over the domain <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>4</mn></math>, the updated design must satisfy the following conditions.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mfenced><mn>4</mn></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mn>3</mn></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down <strong>three</strong> equations, in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math>, using the given conditions.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to substitute one of the given conditions, both <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math>, into either the function or the derivative&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>16</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>b</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to differentiate&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></em><strong>OR</strong><em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> The equations can be found in any order, and hence the associated mark(s) should be awarded independently.</p>\n<p>Accept <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>b</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></math> as correct equations, from symmetry.</p>\n<p>Award at most <em><strong>M1A1M1A1A1A0</strong></em> if the equations are not simplified to integer values.<br>E.g.&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>4</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>b</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></math></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[6 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22631402","referenceCode":"24M.2.SL.TZ1.5e","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down three equations, in terms of a, b and c, using the given conditions.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"e","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 6]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.3—Differentiating polynomials, n E Z","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.8—Use of technology to solve systems of linear equations and polynomial equations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}